We're talking about junk food.
我们要聊的是垃圾食品。

18
00:00:37,800 --> 00:00:42,200
You might argue that it's actually too laid back and is the cause of many problems in
你可能会说这话题太轻松了，而且正是美国和其他地方

19
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:44,800
America and other places in the world.
许多问题的根源。

20
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:46,980
Junk food is unhealthy food.
垃圾食品就是不健康的食物。

21
00:00:46,980 --> 00:00:50,720
So let's take a listen to today's dialogue and we'll be back in a moment to talk about
那么，我们来听听今天的对话，稍后回来再讨论

22
00:00:50,720 --> 00:00:53,720
what's going on.
具体内容。

23
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:58,440
I'm hungry.
我饿了。

24
00:00:58,440 --> 00:00:59,440
Let's go grab a bite to eat.
我们去吃点东西吧。

25
00:00:59,440 --> 00:01:00,440
Sure.
好啊。

26
00:01:00,440 --> 00:01:02,440
How about we go home and prepare a couple of sandwiches?
我们回家做几个三明治怎么样？

27
00:01:02,440 --> 00:01:04,440
Nah, let's get a burger and fries.
不，我们去买个汉堡和薯条吧。

28
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:07,480
What you ever do is have unhealthy fast food.
你总是吃不健康的快餐。

29
00:01:07,480 --> 00:01:09,880
Pizza, fries, burgers and hot dogs.
披萨、薯条、汉堡和热狗。

30
00:01:09,880 --> 00:01:11,320
You have to start eating better.
你得开始吃得更好一点。

31
00:01:11,320 --> 00:01:12,760
What are you talking about?
你在说什么啊？

32
00:01:12,760 --> 00:01:14,080
I have salads sometimes.
我有时候也吃沙拉。

33
00:01:14,080 --> 00:01:15,240
Yeah, right.
是啊，说得对。

34
00:01:15,240 --> 00:01:16,280
I'm serious.
我是认真的。

35
00:01:16,280 --> 00:01:18,960
You should also cut down on your sugar intake as well.
你还应该减少糖分的摄入。

36
00:01:18,960 --> 00:01:21,840
You drink carbonated drinks that are high in fructose syrup.
你喝的那些碳酸饮料果糖含量很高。

37
00:01:21,840 --> 00:01:23,280
It's really not healthy.
真的很不健康。

38
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:24,280
Fine.
好吧。

39
00:01:24,280 --> 00:01:27,040
I'll start drinking water and having home cooked meals that are low in fat.
我会开始喝水，吃低脂的家常菜。

40
00:01:27,040 --> 00:01:28,040
Are you happy now?
你满意了吧？

41
00:01:28,040 --> 00:01:32,560
It's a start but I'll be happy when I see you stick to your promise.
这是个开始，但看到你坚持承诺我才会高兴。

42
00:01:32,560 --> 00:01:36,080
Alright, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

43
00:01:36,080 --> 00:01:40,480
So let's take a look at some of the great words and phrases all about junk food now
现在让我们来看看一些关于垃圾食品的好词好句，

44
00:01:40,480 --> 00:01:44,360
in Language Takeaway.
在“语言小贴士”环节。

45
00:01:44,360 --> 00:01:47,400
Language Takeaway.
语言小贴士。

46
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:48,400
My favorite.
我最喜欢的部分。

47
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:49,400
This stuff makes me hungry.
这些东西让我饿了。

48
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:50,600
But it's not very good for you.
但它对你身体不好。

49
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:51,600
It's not.
确实不好。

50
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:52,600
It's terrible.
太糟糕了。

51
00:01:52,600 --> 00:01:55,160
Actually, his favorite food was burger and fries.
实际上，他最喜欢的食物是汉堡和薯条。

52
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:57,160
I had it for dinner last night.
我昨晚就吃了这个当晚餐。

53
00:01:57,160 --> 00:01:58,160
Really?
真的吗？

54
00:01:58,160 --> 00:01:59,160
You had burger and fries?
你吃了汉堡和薯条？

55
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:00,160
Yeah, maybe.
嗯，也许吧。

56
00:02:00,160 --> 00:02:03,240
Well, it's not very healthy and there's a great way to describe this.
好吧，这不太健康，有一个很好的词可以形容它。

57
00:02:03,240 --> 00:02:04,240
The word is unhealthy.
这个词是“不健康的”。

58
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:07,680
Alright, so yes, as you say, it's very unhealthy.
好的，所以是的，就像你说的，它非常不健康。

59
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:09,960
Well, yeah, because you get fat.
嗯，是啊，因为你会变胖。

60
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:11,240
They're very high in calories.
它们热量很高。

61
00:02:11,240 --> 00:02:12,680
So it's unhealthy.
所以不健康。

62
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:14,280
So that means it's not good for you.
意思就是对你不好。

63
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:15,280
That's right.
没错。

64
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:21,780
So just a reminder, in English, when we hear the word unhealthy or unhappy, this means
所以提醒一下，在英语中，当我们听到“unhealthy”或“unhappy”时，这表示

65
00:02:21,780 --> 00:02:24,400
not healthy, not happy.
不健康、不开心。

66
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:26,840
Un is a prefix that means not.
“Un”是一个前缀，表示“不”。

67
00:02:26,840 --> 00:02:31,560
Okay, and talking about unhealthy food, in general, what are we talking about?
好的，说到不健康的食物，一般来说，我们在说什么？

68
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:33,280
We're talking about fast food.
我们在说快餐。

69
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:37,080
Okay, so this might require a story.
好的，这可能需要一个故事来解释。

70
00:02:37,080 --> 00:02:40,800
What is the meaning behind fast food as opposed to slow food?
“快餐”相对于“慢餐”有什么含义？

71
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,720
Because there is no slow food, right?
因为并没有慢餐这种东西，对吧？

72
00:02:42,720 --> 00:02:45,480
I think now they have it in like France or something like that.
我想现在法国之类的地方有。

73
00:02:45,480 --> 00:02:47,360
They talk about slow food.
他们谈论慢餐。

74
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:50,600
But anyways, fast food is food that is prepared very quickly.
但不管怎样，快餐是准备得很快的食物。

75
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:55,320
So you go, you order, in two or three minutes, you have your entire order ready to go.
所以你去点餐，两三分钟，你点的所有东西就准备好了。

76
00:02:55,320 --> 00:03:01,080
Okay, so maybe this is the food that I could get at McDonald's or Burger King where they
好的，所以这可能是我在麦当劳或汉堡王能买到的食物，他们

77
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:07,480
make it very, very quickly and I can go home or I can go to the office with my food ready.
做得非常快，我可以带回家或带到办公室，食物已经准备好了。

78
00:03:07,480 --> 00:03:08,480
Exactly.
没错。

79
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:13,880
So fast food, very popular among countries, very popular nowadays among busy people who
所以快餐在很多国家很流行，现在在忙碌的人群中也很流行，他们

80
00:03:13,880 --> 00:03:18,480
have no time to sit down at a restaurant or eat or sit down and have a proper lunch.
没时间坐下来在餐厅吃饭，或者坐下来好好吃顿午餐。

81
00:03:18,480 --> 00:03:19,760
Fast food.
快餐。

82
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:25,840
And one of the important drinks at a fast food restaurant is a carbonated drink.
快餐店里一种重要的饮品是碳酸饮料。

83
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:28,160
So this carbonated, what does this mean?
那么“carbonated”是什么意思？

84
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:32,880
This is actually the fancy word for soda or for fizzy drink.
这其实是“苏打水”或“气泡饮料”的正式说法。

85
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:33,880
Fizzy, okay.
气泡的，好的。

86
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:36,360
So something that's carbonated has bubbles.
所以碳酸饮料就是有气泡的东西。

87
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,640
Yeah, it has bubbles.
对，它有气泡。

88
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:41,040
For example, a lot of Europeans drink carbonated water.
比如，很多欧洲人喝碳酸水。

89
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:43,520
That means water with bubbles in it.
就是带气泡的水。

90
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:44,520
That's right.
没错。

91
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:49,440
So actually, the bubbles are caused because the drink has a high concentration of a certain
实际上，气泡的产生是因为饮料中某种气体浓度很高，

92
00:03:49,440 --> 00:03:51,360
gas such as carbon.
比如碳。

93
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:55,240
So that's why it has all these bubbles and it's fizzy like Coca-Cola for example.
所以它才会有这么多气泡，像可口可乐那样。

94
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:58,640
Right, Coca-Cola or Sprite, these are carbonated drinks.
对，可口可乐或雪碧，这些都是碳酸饮料。

95
00:03:58,640 --> 00:03:59,640
Very good.
很好。

96
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:02,160
So you have carbonated water and you have carbonated soda.
所以有碳酸水和碳酸苏打。

97
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:05,000
What is the thing that makes soda different?
那苏打水有什么不同呢？

98
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:07,000
What is it that makes soda taste so good?
是什么让苏打水这么好喝？

99
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:14,040
It's sweet and the ingredient that makes it sweet is called fructose syrup.
是甜味，而让它变甜的原料叫果糖浆。

100
00:04:14,040 --> 00:04:16,080
Fructose syrup is essentially sugar.
果糖浆本质上就是糖。

101
00:04:16,080 --> 00:04:18,440
Yeah, and it comes from corn I believe, right?
是啊，而且我觉得它是从玉米里提取的，对吧？

102
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:19,440
That's right.
没错。

103
00:04:19,440 --> 00:04:25,240
So you can also hear the name corn syrup and this is a sweet syrup that comes from corn
所以你也会听到“玉米糖浆”这个名字，这是一种来自玉米的甜味糖浆，

104
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:29,800
that makes drinks like Sprite and Coca-Cola taste so good.
它让雪碧和可口可乐这样的饮料变得那么好喝。

105
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:32,160
It's also very unhealthy for you.
但它对身体也非常不健康。

106
00:04:32,160 --> 00:04:34,720
Yes, because it has a lot of calories.
是的，因为它含有大量卡路里。

107
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:37,960
So that is one of the main ingredients in soda.
所以那是苏打水的主要成分之一。

108
00:04:37,960 --> 00:04:40,200
Now you know you have fructose syrup.
现在你知道果糖糖浆了吧。

109
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:42,560
Alright, so that's all we've got for Language Takeaway.
好了，这就是我们“语言要点”的全部内容。

110
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:44,320
Let's take another listen to today's dialogue.
让我们再听一遍今天的对话。

111
00:04:44,320 --> 00:04:50,000
We'll be back in a second.
我们马上回来。

112
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:51,000
I'm hungry.
我饿了。

113
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,320
Let's go grab a bite to eat.
我们去吃点东西吧。

114
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:53,320
Sure.
好啊。

115
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:55,160
How about we go home and prepare a couple of sandwiches?
我们回家做几个三明治怎么样？

116
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:57,120
Nah, let's get a burger and fries.
不，我们去买个汉堡和薯条吧。

117
00:04:57,120 --> 00:05:00,000
All you ever do is have unhealthy fast food.
你总是吃那些不健康的快餐。

118
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:02,360
Pizza, fries, burgers and hot dogs.
披萨、薯条、汉堡和热狗。

119
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:03,840
You have to start eating better.
你得开始吃得健康点了。

120
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:05,240
What are you talking about?
你在说什么呢？

121
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:06,760
I have salad sometimes.
我有时候会吃沙拉。

122
00:05:06,760 --> 00:05:07,760
Yeah, right.
是啊，说得轻巧。

123
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:08,760
I'm serious.
我是认真的。

124
00:05:08,760 --> 00:05:11,460
You should also cut down on your sugar intake as well.
你还应该减少糖分的摄入。

125
00:05:11,460 --> 00:05:14,360
You drink carbonated drinks that are high in fructose syrup.
你喝的那些碳酸饮料果糖浆含量很高。

126
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:15,720
It's really not healthy.
那真的不健康。

127
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:16,720
Fine.
好吧。

128
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:19,640
I'll start drinking water and having home-cooked meals that are low in fat.
我会开始喝水，吃低脂的家常菜。

129
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:20,640
Are you happy now?
你现在满意了吧？

130
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:24,720
It's a start, but I'll be happy when I see you stick to your promise.
这是个开始，但看到你坚持承诺我才会高兴。

131
00:05:24,720 --> 00:05:27,900
Alright, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

132
00:05:27,900 --> 00:05:31,800
So now we have a couple of great phrases that we heard along the dialogue.
现在我们在对话中听到了一些很棒的短语。

133
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:36,080
So let's take a look at those now in Fluency Builder.
那我们现在在流利度构建环节来看看这些短语。

134
00:05:36,080 --> 00:05:37,080
Fluency Builder.
流利度构建。

135
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:38,960
Alright, so starting off.
好的，首先开始。

136
00:05:38,960 --> 00:05:43,200
This is a very interesting phrase because we saw it in the first sentence and it says,
这是一个非常有趣的短语，因为我们在第一句话中看到它，它说，

137
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:45,680
let's go grab a bite to eat.
我们去随便吃点东西吧。

138
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:47,720
Let's grab a bite to eat.
我们去随便吃点东西吧。

139
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:53,240
So to grab is to hold something with your hand, okay, to do it quickly.
所以“grab”是用手抓住某物，表示快速做某事。

140
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:54,600
He grabbed my arm.
他抓住了我的胳膊。

141
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:59,080
So to grab a bite to eat, a bite is a small taste.
所以“grab a bite to eat”中的“bite”指的是一小口。

142
00:05:59,080 --> 00:06:01,980
We're going to have a quick meal.
我们要快速吃一顿饭。

143
00:06:01,980 --> 00:06:04,960
So after work, you want to go grab a bite to eat?
所以下班后，你想去随便吃点东西吗？

144
00:06:04,960 --> 00:06:06,960
That means let's go have something to eat quickly.
意思是让我们去快速吃点东西。

145
00:06:06,960 --> 00:06:08,480
Yeah, I'll be there soon.
好的，我马上就到。

146
00:06:08,480 --> 00:06:10,160
Let me just grab a bite to eat.
让我先随便吃点东西。

147
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:11,800
So bite is a little bit.
所以“bite”就是一点点。

148
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:13,900
It's a small amount of food.
它指的是少量食物。

149
00:06:13,900 --> 00:06:17,920
Now for our next phrase, it's very important because I've noticed that a lot of our English
现在来看下一个短语，它非常重要，因为我注意到很多英语

150
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:21,000
learners make the mistake of using this phrase.
学习者会误用这个短语。

151
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,720
It's how about.
就是“how about”。

152
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:23,720
How about.
“How about”。

153
00:06:23,720 --> 00:06:30,000
So in today's dialogue, the phrase is, how about we go home and prepare a couple of sandwiches?
所以在今天的对话中，这个短语是：我们回家做几个三明治怎么样？

154
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:36,080
So how about is used as a suggestion is, how do you feel or what do you think of going
所以“how about”用作建议时，意思是：你觉得回家做几个三明治怎么样？

155
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:37,560
home and preparing a couple of sandwiches?
或者你对回家做几个三明治有什么看法？

156
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:42,000
So another way to say this is, why don't we go home and prepare some sandwiches?
所以另一种说法是：我们为什么不回家做些三明治呢？

157
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:43,000
Exactly.
没错。

158
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:49,720
But commonly, English learners make the mistake of using how about as a way of saying how
但通常，英语学习者会误用“how about”来表示“how was it”或“how is it”。

159
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:51,440
was it or how is it.
比如，你的周末怎么样？

160
00:06:51,440 --> 00:06:54,520
So for example, how about your weekend?
例如，你的周末过得怎么样？

161
00:06:54,520 --> 00:06:55,520
Wrong.
错了。

162
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:56,520
Okay.
好的。

163
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:58,240
So how was your weekend?
那你周末过得怎么样？

164
00:06:58,240 --> 00:06:59,240
Exactly.
没错。

165
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:03,640
So how about is usually used when we make a suggestion.
所以“how about”通常用于提出建议。

166
00:07:03,640 --> 00:07:07,000
How about we go see a movie on Saturday?
我们周六去看电影怎么样？

167
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:10,680
Or how about we go to my parents' house for Christmas this year?
或者今年圣诞节去我父母家怎么样？

168
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:16,720
Or finally, how about you get another job so that we can have more money to spend on
或者最后，你换份工作怎么样，这样我们就有更多钱花在

169
00:07:16,720 --> 00:07:18,200
going out to eat?
外出吃饭上？

170
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:19,200
Very good.
很好。

171
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:20,660
So how about, these are all suggestions.
所以“how about”这些都是建议。

172
00:07:20,660 --> 00:07:22,080
Why don't you get another job?
你为什么不换份工作？

173
00:07:22,080 --> 00:07:25,300
Why don't we go to our parents' house for Christmas?
我们为什么不去父母家过圣诞节？

174
00:07:25,300 --> 00:07:29,280
So you can't say, how about your weekend?
所以你不能说“how about your weekend？”

175
00:07:29,280 --> 00:07:30,940
You say, how was your weekend?
你要说“how was your weekend？”

176
00:07:30,940 --> 00:07:32,380
So there's a big difference there.
所以这里有很大的区别。

177
00:07:32,380 --> 00:07:33,380
Very good.
很好。

178
00:07:33,380 --> 00:07:36,960
So make sure to stay away from that typical mistake using how about.
所以一定要避免那个常见的错误，不要用“how about”那样说。

179
00:07:36,960 --> 00:07:41,760
Now moving on, we were talking about fast food and how it's bad for you and she said,
现在继续，我们之前谈到快餐对健康不好，然后她说，

180
00:07:41,760 --> 00:07:42,760
you know what?
你知道吗？

181
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:46,000
You should also cut down on your sugar intake.
你还应该减少糖的摄入量。

182
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:48,680
So to cut down, that's a phrasal verb.
所以“cut down”是一个短语动词。

183
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:49,680
That's right.
没错。

184
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:50,720
Cut down.
减少。

185
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:53,440
So that means to decrease.
意思是减少。

186
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:57,800
I'm trying to cut down on the amount of soda that I drink.
我正在努力减少喝汽水的量。

187
00:07:57,800 --> 00:08:02,000
Or I'm trying to cut down on how much I spend on the weekends.
或者我正在努力减少周末的花费。

188
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,000
Okay.
好的。

189
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:06,320
So to cut down means to decrease or to lessen.
所以“cut down”意思是减少或降低。

190
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:07,320
Very good.
很好。

191
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:11,240
And for our last phrase, the whole thing that we're talking about and one of the favorite
至于我们最后一个短语，我们一直在谈论的，也是大家最喜欢的

192
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:13,880
meals for everyone, burger and fries.
餐点之一，汉堡和薯条。

193
00:08:13,880 --> 00:08:14,880
Okay.
好的。

194
00:08:14,880 --> 00:08:17,660
So this is one of many combinations for meals.
所以这是众多餐点组合之一。

195
00:08:17,660 --> 00:08:22,920
You can have a burger and fries, which is a hamburger and French fries.
你可以点汉堡和薯条，也就是汉堡和炸薯条。

196
00:08:22,920 --> 00:08:27,080
So oftentimes you'll say, hey, let's go grab a burger and fries.
所以通常你会说，嘿，我们去吃个汉堡和薯条吧。

197
00:08:27,080 --> 00:08:30,440
Another combination, especially in England, is fish and chips.
另一种组合，尤其是在英国，是炸鱼薯条。

198
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:31,440
Yeah.
是的。

199
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:32,440
Fish and chips.
炸鱼薯条。

200
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:36,240
Fish would be a fried fish sandwich and chips would be French fries as well.
鱼是炸鱼三明治，薯条也是炸薯条。

201
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:37,240
That's right.
没错。

202
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:41,000
So actually in England, they call French fries, they call them chips.
所以实际上在英国，他们把炸薯条叫做“chips”。

203
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:46,680
So if you're confused by the word chips or potato chips and French fries, these are different
所以如果你对“chips”或“potato chips”和“French fries”这些词感到困惑，这些在不同地方

204
00:08:46,680 --> 00:08:47,980
things in different places.
是不同的东西。

205
00:08:47,980 --> 00:08:52,220
But if you're talking to an American, French fries is the way to go.
但如果你跟美国人说话，用“French fries”就对了。

206
00:08:52,220 --> 00:08:54,040
Or for a while, they were called freedom fries.
或者有一段时间，它们被称为“freedom fries”。

207
00:08:54,040 --> 00:08:55,800
Well, we don't need to talk about that.
嗯，我们不需要讨论那个。

208
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:58,080
We can talk about that in a later lesson.
我们可以在以后的课里讨论。

209
00:08:58,080 --> 00:09:00,840
But for now, the phrase is burger and fries.
但现在，这个短语是“burger and fries”。

210
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:01,840
All right.
好了。

211
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:06,680
Let's listen to our dialogue for the very last time.
让我们最后一次听我们的对话。

212
00:09:06,680 --> 00:09:11,960
I'm hungry.
我饿了。

213
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:12,960
Let's go grab a bite to eat.
我们去吃点东西吧。

214
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:13,960
Sure.
当然。

215
00:09:13,960 --> 00:09:15,960
How about we go home and prepare a couple of sandwiches?
我们回家做几个三明治怎么样？

216
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:17,960
Nah, let's get a burger and fries.
不，我们去吃汉堡和薯条吧。

217
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:20,960
What you ever do is have unhealthy fast food.
你总是吃不健康的快餐。

218
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:23,400
Pizza, fries, burgers, and hot dogs.
披萨、薯条、汉堡和热狗。

219
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:24,840
You have to start eating better.
你得开始吃得更好。

220
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:26,280
What are you talking about?
你在说什么？

221
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:27,840
I have salads sometimes.
我有时候也吃沙拉。

222
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:28,840
Yeah, right.
是啊，说得对。

223
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:29,840
I'm serious.
我是认真的。

224
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:32,480
You should also cut down on your sugar intake as well.
你也应该减少糖的摄入量。

225
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:35,360
You drink carbonated drinks that are high in fructose syrup.
你喝的那些碳酸饮料富含果糖糖浆。

226
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:36,680
It's really not healthy.
真的很不健康。

227
00:09:36,680 --> 00:09:37,680
Fine.
好吧。

228
00:09:37,680 --> 00:09:40,520
I'll start drinking water and having home cooked meals that are low in fat.
我会开始喝水，吃低脂的家常菜。

229
00:09:40,520 --> 00:09:41,520
Are you happy now?
你现在满意了吗？

230
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:51,240
It's a start, but I'll be happy when I see you stick to your promise.
这是个开始，但看到你遵守承诺我才会高兴。

231
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:52,240
We're back, Marco.
我们回来了，Marco。

232
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:53,240
You're laughing.
你在笑。

233
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:54,320
I know you like junk food.
我知道你喜欢垃圾食品。

234
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:57,120
What's your favorite junk food of all time?
你一直以来最喜欢的垃圾食品是什么？

235
00:09:57,120 --> 00:10:01,400
Actually, I am a big, big fan of fried chicken.
其实，我是炸鸡的超级粉丝。

236
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:03,800
I love fried chicken.
我喜欢炸鸡。

237
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:04,800
Yummy.
好吃。

238
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:05,800
I don't know.
我不知道。

239
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:10,120
I think it's really greasy and oily and it's very, very bad, but I can't help it.
我觉得它很油腻，非常非常不健康，但我控制不住。

240
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:11,120
It's very good.
它太好吃了。

241
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:12,120
You can buy bags of it in America.
在美国你可以买整袋的。

242
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:13,120
I know.
我知道。

243
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:14,480
You can get like a pound bag of fried chicken.
你可以买到一磅装的炸鸡。

244
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:16,800
You buy it by the pound in America, right?
在美国是按磅买的，对吧？

245
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:17,800
Yep.
对。

246
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:19,120
You pay for how much it weighs.
你按重量付钱。

247
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:20,120
Wow.
哇。

248
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:21,120
That's amazing.
太棒了。

249
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:24,200
I actually really enjoy it, but places like Kentucky Fried Chicken, they're too expensive
我其实挺喜欢的，但像肯德基那样的地方，炸鸡太贵了。

250
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:25,800
for fried chicken.
对于炸鸡来说。

251
00:10:25,800 --> 00:10:28,160
Yeah, you don't necessarily want to go there.
是啊，没必要非去那里。

252
00:10:28,160 --> 00:10:33,200
There's other places that are a lot more maybe traditional that are pretty good.
还有其他更传统的地方，味道也不错。

253
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:34,200
How about you?
你呢？

254
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,600
What is your favorite junk food?
你最喜欢的垃圾食品是什么？

255
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:40,000
Chicago-style hot dog and french fries.
芝加哥风味热狗和薯条。

256
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:43,760
When you go to see a baseball game, you get a hot dog, but Chicago-style is good.
去看棒球赛时，你会吃热狗，但芝加哥风味的不错。

257
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:45,400
It's not too much stuff on it.
上面放的东西不多。

258
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:51,360
You have a poppy seed bun, so it's a bun, a piece of bread with some seeds on it and
用的是罂粟籽面包，就是那种带籽的面包，还有

259
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:55,640
a lot of mustard and ketchup and onions.
很多芥末、番茄酱和洋葱。

260
00:10:55,640 --> 00:11:01,160
I really enjoy hot dogs, but the one thing that I cannot have on a hot dog is mustard
我很喜欢热狗，但唯一不能接受的是热狗上放芥末

261
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:02,160
or relish.
或酸黄瓜酱。

262
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:03,160
Oh my gosh.
哦，天哪。

263
00:11:03,160 --> 00:11:04,840
Those are the two best things.
那可是最好吃的两样东西。

264
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:06,680
Okay, I can't talk to you anymore.
好吧，我不能再跟你说话了。

265
00:11:06,680 --> 00:11:11,760
Well, tell us what your favorite junk food is and tell Marco that he's crazy if he doesn't
那么，告诉我们你最喜欢的垃圾食品是什么，并告诉马可，如果他不喜欢芥末，他就是疯了。

266
00:11:11,760 --> 00:11:13,440
like mustard.
不喜欢芥末。

267
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:15,200
Our website is EnglishPod.com.
我们的网站是EnglishPod.com。

268
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:16,200
Ask us questions as well.
也欢迎向我们提问。

269
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,840
We're happy to answer them.
我们很乐意回答。

270
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:18,840
Until next time.
下次再见。

271
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:19,840
Bye, everyone.
大家再见。

272
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:25,840
Thanks for watching.
感谢观看。
